org.ow2.bonita.facade.def.majorElement
Interface TransitionDefinition

All Superinterfaces:
DescriptionElement, NamedElement, ProcessElement, Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
TransitionDefinitionImpl
public interface TransitionDefinition
extends ProcessElement, Serializable

Activities are linked themselves using transition. A transition links only two activities. Three kinf of tranistion exists:

  • Normal transition
  • Default transition
  • Exception transition
A normal transition is a transition which can contains a condition. If the condition is true, the transition is taken.
A default transition is a transition which is taken when no other transitions can be taken.
And an exception transition links a boundary event of an activity to another activity.
